---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
    title="About Us | Macomb County Realty" 
    description="We don't push you towards a lowball cash offer or force you to list on the market, you get to pick. We are your local real estate solutions provider."
>
    <main>

        <section class="benefits-section about-hero-section">
            <div class="benefits-container">
                <div class="benefits-header about-hero-header">
                    <h1 class="benefits-title about-hero-title">
                        Sell Your House.&nbsp;
                        <span class="premium-underline">Your Way.</span>
                    </h1>

                    <p class="benefits-subtitle about-hero-subtitle">
                        As licensed real estate professionals, we offer both cash purchases and traditional listings.
                        We'll walk you through both options, then you decide.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section-padding">
            <div class="benefits-container">
                <div class="benefits-header about-header-margin">
                    <h2 class="benefits-title">
                        Why We Started
                    </h2>
                    <p class="benefits-subtitle">
                        We believe homeowners deserve better than the standard "take it or leave it" approach.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="way-split-grid">
                    
                    <!-- Card 1: The Old Way -->
                    <div class="way-card old-way">
                        <div class="way-card-header">
                            <div class="way-icon">⚠️</div>
                            <h3 class="way-title">The "Old" Way</h3>
                        </div>
                        <ul class="way-list">
                            <li>
                                <strong>Only One Option</strong> 
                                You're cornered into either taking a lowball cash offer or forced to list on the market.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Hidden Agendas</strong> 
                                Companies push the solution that makes <em>them</em> the most money, not you.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>High Pressure</strong> 
                                Aggressive tactics to get you to sign quickly before you truly understand your choices.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Card 2: Our Way -->
                    <div class="way-card our-way">
                        <div class="way-card-header">
                            <div class="way-icon">🤝</div>
                            <h3 class="way-title">The Macomb County Realty Way</h3>
                        </div>
                        <ul class="way-list">
                            <li>
                                <strong>You Pick</strong> 
                                Compare a competitive cash offer side-by-side with listing on the open market.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Honest Guidance</strong> 
                                As licensed professionals and local buyers, we explain both paths transparently.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <strong>Total Control</strong> 
                                No pressure. We empower you to make the best decision for your unique financial situation.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </section>


<section class="about-section-padding bg-light-gray">
    <div class="benefits-container">
        <!-- Section Header -->
        <div class="benefits-header about-header-margin" style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 40px;">
            <h2 class="benefits-title">
                Why Homeowners Choose Us
            </h2>
            <p class="benefits-subtitle">
                Selling your home should be simple, transparent, and built around your goals.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- 4-Column Card Grid -->
        <div class="choose-us-grid">
            
            <!-- Card 1 -->
            <div class="choose-card">
                <div class="choose-card-header">
                    <div class="choose-icon">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                            <path d="M3 9l9-7 9 7v11a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2z"></path>
                            <polyline points="9 22 9 12 15 12 15 22"></polyline>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Two Selling Options</h3>
                </div>
                <p>Compare the highest cash offer with the option of listing your home on the open market, all with one trusted team.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2 -->
            <div class="choose-card">
                <div class="choose-card-header">
                    <div class="choose-icon">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle>
                            <polygon points="16.24 7.76 14.12 14.12 7.76 16.24 9.88 9.88 16.24 7.76"></polygon>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Honest Guidance</h3>
                </div>
                <p>We'll recommend the option that makes the most sense for your situation, not simply the one that benefits us.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 3 -->
            <div class="choose-card">
                <div class="choose-card-header">
                    <div class="choose-icon">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                            <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3>No Pressure</h3>
                </div>
                <p>Ask questions, compare your options, and move forward only when you're comfortable. There's no obligation.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 4 -->
            <div class="choose-card">
                <div class="choose-card-header">
                    <div class="choose-icon">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                            <path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0 1 18 0z"></path>
                            <circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"></circle>
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Local Experience</h3>
                </div>
                <p>We've helped homeowners throughout Metro Detroit navigate inherited homes, difficult situations, and everything in between.</p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</section>








        <section class="team-section">
    <div class="team-container">
        
        <div class="team-header">
            <h2 class="benefits-title">Meet The Team</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="team-grid">

            <div class="team-card">
                <img 
                    src="/images/nonno-headshot-about-page.webp" 
                    alt="Domenic Mancini" 
                    loading="lazy" 
                    class="team-img" 
                />
                <div class="team-card-content">
                    <h3 class="team-name">Domenic Mancini</h3>
                    <p class="team-role">Founder</p>
                    <p class="team-bio">
                        Every family business has someone who started it all. Domenic began his career as a superintendent overseeing major public works projects before turning his attention to homebuilding. He went on to build numerous homes throughout Fraser, Michigan—including the home he still lives in today. Now in his 90s, Domenic's work ethic and values continue to shape our business. His favorite saying is "Primum vivere, deinde philosophari," meaning, "First live, then philosophize."
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="team-card">
                <img 
                    src="/images/dad-headshot-about-page.webp" 
                    alt="Max Mancini Sr." 
                    loading="lazy" 
                    class="team-img" 
                />
                <div class="team-card-content">
                    <h3 class="team-name">Massimo Mancini</h3>
                    <p class="team-role">Broker</p>
                    <p class="team-bio">
                        Massimo (Max) grew up around construction, learning the trade alongside his father while helping build the family home. Today, he is the <a href="https://aca-prod.accela.com/MILARA/GeneralProperty/LicenseeDetail.aspx?LicenseeNumber=6502431655&LicenseeType=Real+Estate+Principal+Associate+Broker" target="_blank" class="hyper-link"><strong>broker of Macomb County Realty</strong></a>, a licensed builder, and an active real estate investor. Having built some of Macomb's finest custom homes, Max brings decades of construction knowledge, market expertise, and honest guidance to every client. When he's not helping clients, Max enjoys trying new things and believes you're never too old to learn something new.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="team-card">
                <img 
                    src="/images/max-headshot-about-page.jpg" 
                    alt="Max Mancini Jr." 
                    loading="lazy" 
                    class="team-img bg-light" 
                />
                <div class="team-card-content">
                    <h3 class="team-name">Max Mancini</h3>
                    <p class="team-role">Agent</p>
                    <p class="team-bio">
                        As the third generation of the Mancini family in real estate, Max is proud to continue the tradition. A <a href="https://aca-prod.accela.com/MILARA/GeneralProperty/LicenseeDetail.aspx?LicenseeNumber=6501454853&LicenseeType=Real+Estate+Salesperson" target="_blank" class="hyper-link"><strong>licensed real estate agent</strong></a> and engineer (Go Blue!), he focuses on business operations while expanding his experience in property renovation and investment. Whether helping homeowners explore their selling options or improving the company's operations, Max is committed to making the process simple and stress-free. Outside of work, he enjoys playing soccer and has a passion for cars.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="final-cta-section">
        <div class="cta-container">
            <h2 class="cta-heading cta-heading-about">
                Ready to Sell Your House? 
            </h2>
            <p class="cta-subheading">
                Take the first step toward a stress-free sale today.
            </p>

            <div class="cta-actions">
                <a href="/contact" class="comparison-cta-btn"
                    >Get My Options ➔</a
                >

                <p class="cta-secondary-text final-cta-phone">
                    <strong>Call or Text:</strong><br />
                    <a href="tel:+15864157355" class="cta-phone-link"
                        >(586) 415–7355</a
                    >
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>


    </main>
</Layout>